{
  "texts": [
    "Modularity: quantifying transition probabilities between cells is independent of analyzing them.",
    "Thus, we modularized the CellRank framework into kernels to compute transition probabilities and estimators to analyze transition probabilities.",
    "This structure guarantees flexibility in applications and is easily extensible. 3.",
    "Scalability: we assume each cell can transition into a small set of possible descendant states.",
    "Consequently, transition matrices are sparse, and computations scale to vast cell numbers (Extended Data Fig. 2)."
  ]
}